<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-04-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-04-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="431" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d431">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">812.113/10500: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Ciudad Juarez</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dye</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">El
                                        Paso, Tex</hi></placeName>., <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-04-01">April 1, 1929</date>.<lb/>[Received 7:23
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Rebels in Juarez claim to have there nine airplanes. Believe this is
                            exaggerated. Am reliably informed they bought three planes in <pb facs="0495" n="377" xml:id="pg_377"/> Phoenix, paying $7,000 apiece,
                            and one trimotor in Los Angeles. These planes crossed to Mexico from El
                            Paso Friday and Saturday nights with American pilots. Rebels seem to
                            have plenty of money and is open secret that much ammunition and
                            materials crossing to Mexico.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dye</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>